{#- DEFINITION — plain-terms prose body -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="qb-help-speak-expert-definition" style="padding-top:24px;">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="eyebrow" style="margin-bottom:8px;">In plain terms</div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">What &ldquo;speak to a QuickBooks expert&rdquo; really means here.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>A &ldquo;QuickBooks expert,&rdquo; in the way most people mean it, is someone who can look at <em>your</em> books and tell you what&rsquo;s actually wrong &mdash; and fix it. At an independent firm like TechBrot, that person is a Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor: an accounting professional who holds the ProAdvisor certification from Intuit and works inside QuickBooks files every day. The certification is held <em>from</em> Intuit; it does not make us part of Intuit, and we don&rsquo;t represent Intuit.</p>
      <p>That distinction matters because it tells you which problems we can help with. If your file is broken, behind, or unreconciled &mdash; or you&rsquo;re setting up, migrating, or just trying to decide whether you need help &mdash; that&rsquo;s the conversation to have with a ProAdvisor. If the issue is your Intuit account, your subscription, your login, your billing, or a bug in the QuickBooks software itself, that&rsquo;s Intuit&rsquo;s to resolve, and an independent firm simply can&rsquo;t reach into your Intuit account. This page is the honest entry point; the fuller picture of how working with a ProAdvisor goes lives on our <a href="/quickbooks/speak-to-a-quickbooks-expert/">speak to a QuickBooks expert</a> page.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

